course_description: Application and synthesis of knowledge from pathophysiology, embryology and other sciences in assessment, differential diagnoses, comprehensive care management and evaluation across the continuum (acute-critical-chronic care), for the entire neonatal population foci.
prerequisites: NRSG 609D prerequisite and NRSG  610D co-requisite or equivalent transfer credit. Students must enroll in NRSG 610D first.
